condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Loan Agreement, Schedule 2, Section II.A.1 | Description :The Project Implementing Entity shall monitor andevaluate the progress of the Project and prepare semi-annual Project Progress Reports on the basis of indicators agreed with theBank and set forth in the Operational Manual. Each such Report shall cover the period of one calendar semester, and shall befurnished to the Borrower not later than Feb 15 and Aug 15 each year, starting on Feb 15, 2014. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Loan Agreement, Schedule 2, Section II.B.3 | Description :The Project Implementing Entity shall appoint externaland independent auditors satisfactory to the Bank and have the appointed auditors to carry out annual audits no later than sixmonths after the end of the fiscal year. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Project Agreement, Schedule 2, Section I.A.3 | Description :The Project Implementing Entity shall furnish to theBank for approval, an initial work and budget plan covering the first eighteenmonths of Project implementation; and an annualimplementation plan by December 15 each year, beginning on December 15, 2014. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Project Agreement, Schedule 2, Section II.A.3 | Description :The Project Implementing Entity shall, uponcompletion of selected Project activities (as these are programmed and set forth in theOperational Manual), cause each of therelevant Project Cities to prepare and furnish to the Bank (and continue to do so by January31 of each calendar year thereafter),an annual operation and maintenance plan for project financed assets. | Frequency :Yearly
